reviews: Front cover does scratch kinda easy, other con is the rubber that goes into usb c after your dont charging you phone it won't go in side and stay, about three long press it will eventually stay in for the most part..
Omg best thing ever to bring camping... strong enough it won't rip on you... bum feels very happy after each use... Ppl you have to buy this, you'll be thanking me later...

ya doesn't work, don't waste your money on this..

☆☆
Not too happy, end up buying 3 of these to find out battery life sucks, went camping sept long weekend to find out i basically had to plug these into my power bank the whole time I was there... 12hrs of battery life.... ah no, more like 4hrs.. I understand volume on full blast can eat a bunch of the battery but.... but..... the sound quality and bass is very impressive, should've saved up for the soundcore 2, I hear such good things bout that one...

Update☆☆☆☆
5 stars for Customer service... Anker has reached out to me and gave me an upgrad for my trouble, so the soundcore 2 I must say has an amazing battery life but the sound quality is nothing like the icon... At the end of the day I'd rather have the soundcore 2 its super solid and battery life is what I'm looking for, and with ok sound..
First time I had anything negative to say about anker products and they made it right, nice to see a company that stands behind there products and want to make the customer happy...
Works great I highly recommend
not the best quality but it works
Entertaining

review_title: Its a name you can trust on

First off its pretty much a hand wipe but an upgrade to cloth of some kind..
Does clean pretty well, doesn't fold into itself when cleaning your face or arms, if that makes sense...
My only Con is the smell, apparently I have 4 more months left to expiration date.. So this smell to me is somewhere between baby Diarrhea and or that smell when you leave your wet clothes in a washer machine for couple of days... After you wash your face your kinda like guessing where you have smelled this before...
I'll be staying with dude wipes, they cost more but atleast you feel clean afterwards with no smell...
After a year of use not one problem... easy to clean, fast flow rate..

Only con and most bells this style have the same issue is the part that actually hits the bell sometimes it moves outta place and you have to adjust it before it works, simple superglue fixed that problem...

Wow factor...
